</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[160,1155,640,802]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1459">
According to the literature, the fauna of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1870" box="[624,740,640,664]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="1459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hersiliidae</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[778,821,640,664]" name="Iran" pageId="13" pageNumber="1459">Iran</collectingCountry>
should be considered poorly studied (
<bibRefCitation author="Mirshamsi O &amp; Marusik YM &amp; Jamili E" box="[259,504,674,698]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1459" pagination="347 - 352" refId="ref4893" refString="Mirshamsi O, Marusik YM, Jamili E. 2013. The spider family Hersiliidae Thorell, 1870 (Arachnida: Araneae) in Iran. Zool Middle East. 59: 347 - 352." type="journal article" year="2013">Mirshamsi et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). The first records of these spiders in the Iranian Plateau have been recently provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marusik YM &amp; Fet V" box="[548,818,709,733]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1459" pagination="75 - 114" refId="ref4820" refString="Marusik YM, Fet V. 2009. A survey of East Palearctic Hersiliola Thorell, 1870 (Araneae: Hersiliidae), with description of three new genera. Zookeys. 16: 75 - 114." type="journal article" year="2009">Marusik and Fet (2009)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Mirshamsi O &amp; Marusik YM &amp; Jamili E" box="[884,1151,709,733]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1459" pagination="347 - 352" refId="ref4893" refString="Mirshamsi O, Marusik YM, Jamili E. 2013. The spider family Hersiliidae Thorell, 1870 (Arachnida: Araneae) in Iran. Zool Middle East. 59: 347 - 352." type="journal article" year="2013">Mirshamsi et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mirshamsi O &amp; Marusik YM &amp; Jamili E" box="[160,420,744,768]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1459" pagination="347 - 352" refId="ref4893" refString="Mirshamsi O, Marusik YM, Jamili E. 2013. The spider family Hersiliidae Thorell, 1870 (Arachnida: Araneae) in Iran. Zool Middle East. 59: 347 - 352." type="journal article" year="2013">Mirshamsi et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
listed five species from the country, which showed the highest species diversity of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1870" box="[384,500,778,802]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="1459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hersiliidae</taxonomicName>
in the Palaearctic region.
</paragraph>
