<paragraph blockId="14.[160,1156,142,478]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460">
The results of this study increase the number of hersiliids of 
<collectingCountry box="[892,935,142,166]" name="Iran" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460">Iran</collectingCountry>
to eight species in four genera: 
<taxonomicName authority="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2016" authorityName="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2016" box="[312,563,177,201]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Bastanius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kermanensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[312,563,177,201]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460">Bastanius kermanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[574,667,177,201]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[681,777,177,201]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foordi">B. foordi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[793,980,177,201]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Duninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baehrae">Duninia baehrae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mirshamsi &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2013" box="[996,1117,177,201]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Duninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="darvishi">D. darvishi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Duninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rheimsae">D. rheimsae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2016" authorityName="Mirshamsi &amp; Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2016" box="[273,428,212,236]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Hersilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talebii" status="sp. nov.">Hersilia talebii</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[437,527,212,236]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[539,765,212,236]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sternbergsi">
<emphasis box="[539,765,212,236]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460">Hersiliola sternbergsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dufour" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[825,985,212,236]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macullulata">
<emphasis box="[825,985,212,236]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460">H. macullulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Figure 6).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[160,1156,142,478]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460">
Although all of the above species are morphologically distinct, the application of molecular markers, such as cytochrome c oxidase, subunit I (
<emphasis box="[895,934,281,305]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1460">COI</emphasis>
), may lead to the discovery of more new species of this taxon in this geographic area. Furthermore, considering the fact that comprehensive faunistic studies on spiders in much of the Iranian Plateau and Zagros Mountains have not been conducted, any newly collected material from these regions is therefore valuable and may represent new records or species.
</paragraph>
